	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't know about this particular board and ROM hack, but the first place I'd check are the CHR address outputs from the MMC3.  CHR A13 and A14 in particular.
<br />
<br />Other factors are involved, if you're converting from a CHR-RAM board then you have other CHR lines you may need to connect to the MMC3 (they kind of pass-through the MMC3), that just depends on how the ROM does the bankswitching.
<br />
<br />You'll have to check the MMC3 pinout mostly, trace how it's hooked up the CHR.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
